Forms a unique monophyletic clade distinct from other AB01 specimens. Morphologically fits Ophiomusium cf. glabrum detailed in (
Luetken and Mortensen 1899
) but no genetic data available from type locality (47°22'N; 125°48'W, 1604m depth) ( National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution 2015 ). CO1 sequences of our material is 17% different (K2P distance) from sequences published on Genbank (HM400322-HM400323).
